        <h3><u>Education</u></h3>
        <p> <strong>The United States Department of Education</strong> is a Cabinet-level department of the United States government. It began operating on May 4, 1980, having been created after the Department of Health, Education, and Welfare was split into the Department of Education and the Department of Health and Human Services by the Department of Education Organization Act, which President Jimmy Carter signed into law on October 17, 1979. </p>
        <p>For more information click on <a style="color: yellow;" href="https://www.ed.gov/"><strong>United States Department of Education</strong></a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <br/>

